  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing the Economic and Political Empowerment of Women in the Sava</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With only 11% having any formal education, women are severely under-represented at all levels of government and decision-making in the deprived Northern Region of Ghana. This prevents women from advancing economically or politically. This project provides training and support to women so they have the skills, confidence and abilities to stand in local, district and parliamentary elections. Newly-elected women officials receive mentoring from more experienced peers. Networks and coalitions are organised so that women can effectively get their voices heard on issues of policy. The project actively involves community leaders, traditional chiefs and all the political parties to garner their support for this initiative. As a result women&apos;s representation and participation in decision-making at all levels will increase.</narrative>
  </description>
